    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-03-09T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-03-09T01:00:00-05:00" n="578"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d578">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/4638: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai (<persName corresp="#p_CES1"
                            type="from">Cunningham</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-09T14:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 9, 1932—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 9—8:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>172. Following from Captain <persName corresp="#p_MCW1">Mayer</persName> for War
                    Department.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“27. <persName corresp="#p_SGY1">Shirakawa</persName> announced a zone in
                        front of Japanese outpost line in which Japanese patrols will operate and in
                        which if Chinese troops are found a clash might result. Western limits of
                        patrol zone are Fuchiao-Yuehwangshih-Waikang-Anting-Paihuchiang. South of
                        Soochow Creek Japanese have detachments at <persName corresp="#p_TVAT1"
                            >Toyoda</persName> mill and Siccawei just west and southwest of the
                        Settlement. Half of 14th Division has landed balance en route, it is
                        reported they will relieve 9th Division which will remain in reserve.
                        Hangchow Railway resumed operation March 7.”</p>
                </quote>
                <p>Repeated to the Legation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CES1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cunningham</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
